						<div class="postbody">I have to agree with infiniteneslives; once you're building <em>any</em> hardware, you should use something that's less obnoxious (and higher bandwidth) than the data recorder.<br /><br />If compactflash weren't horribly moribund I'd vote for it because it combines &quot;minimal support hardware&quot; with &quot;ubiquitous&quot;, but we're close to ten years too late. SD would be good but requires much more support hardware. I agree that the next best combination of &quot;cheap&quot; and &quot;easy for the end user&quot; is most likely some high speed PC interface, especially if it's either combinable with the CIC or the mapper hardware.</div>

