						<div class="postbody">Silly question: what are 2P Start and Select mapped to and what is the microphone mapped to? I wouldn't be surprised if the microphone overlaps at least the bits of one of those buttons - in which case you're pretty much looking at just making a replacement controller. The microphone doesn't seem very reliable anyway...<br /><br />And yeah, if you want to make something that's bound to work everywhere, hardware on the cartridge is the only option (you can't rely on the I/O ports since they differ between the NES and the Famicom, the lightguns don't work, etc.), or if you're transferring small amounts of data, passwords =P</div>

